At the time of claiming entitlement to trade secret protection, the vendor, service provider, or operator shall file with the director the following information on a form prescribed by the division. The form shall include:
The claimant's name, authorized representative, mailing address, and phone number;
The specific information claimed to be entitled to trade secret protection;
Whether there has been a previous determination by a court or by a governmental agency that the information is or is not entitled to confidential treatment; and
The measures taken by the vendor, service provider, or operator to protect the confidentiality of the information.
